      "description": "  ORDER. The following motions are DENIED without prejudice because they were filed on  behalf of the trust, which is no longer a party; or because they relate to or target the original  complaint (or motions related to the original complaint) and are  therefore moot:  - Motion for Partial Summary Judgment  28 ;- Motion for Reconsideration  41 ;- Motion for Sanctions  42 ;- Motion for Default Judgment  43 ;-   Motion to Dismiss (original complaint)  44 ;- Joint Motion to Sta y Case (pending a decision on the motion to dismiss), or Alternative  Motion for Extension of Time  51 ,  52 ;- Motion to Strike  53 ;- Motion for Extension of Time  55 ;- Motion to Extend Time  68 ; and- Motion to Dismiss  74 .The  Clerk of Court is also directed to AMEND the CAPTION and the DOCKET to reflect that  the plaintiff is now Richard Friedman and not the Jackson Hole Bank Fraud Litigation Trust.       Signed by Judge Jennifer A. Dorsey on 9/11/2019.  (no image attached) (Copies have been distributed pursuant to the NEF - DC)"
    },
